TCP/IP is combination of 2 protocols. Transmission Controll Protocol

TCP + Internet Protocol IP IPS





#Internet Protocol Suite

-Appplication Layer (User Application)             // HTTP, SMTP, DNS and others
-Transport Layer				// TCP, UDP and others
-Internet Layer					// Ipv4, IPv6 and others
-Link Layer (Physical layer)			// Ethernet , PPP


*)Link Layer:

Lowest level of layer describe physical mechanisms used to transfer information between nodes on alocal network.
eg:Ethernet

*) Internet Layer

This layer provides the mechanisms for addressing network notes.


*) Transport Layer
Transport layer is resposible for connection between client and servers
TCP and UPD operate in this layer

*) Apllicationn Layer

this layer contains network protocols such as HTTP, SMTP , DNS 


--Each layer interacts only with the layer of two and below, but there is a must be external interaction within the stack




/////////////////////////Example/////////////////////////////////

Mail Application


(clinet)

-> User Interface
HTML Rendering

-> Content Parsers
Text, HTML, JPG

-> Network Communication
SMTP, POP3, IMAP


